Natrelle® Breast Implants are approved for women for the following:   •Breast augmentation for women at least 22 years old for silicone-filled implants.   •Breast augmentation for women at least 18 years old for saline-filled implants. column121: currently taking drugs that weaken the body’s natural resistance to disease).   •Planned chemotherapy following breast implant placement   •Planned radiation therapy to the breast following breast implant placement.   •Conditions or medications that interfere with wound healing and blood clotting.   •Reduced blood supply to breast tissue.   •Clinical diagnosis of depression or other mental health disorders
column122: including body dysmorphic disorder and eating disorders. Please discuss any history of mental health disorders with your surgeon prior to surgery. Patients with a diagnosis of depression or other mental health disorders should wait for resolution or stabilization of these conditions prior to undergoing breast implantation surgery.   What are some complications with breast implants?  Key complications are reoperation
column123: implant removal with or without replacement
column126: and severe capsular contracture (severe scar tissue around the implant). Other complications include asymmetry
column128: scarring or wrinkling/rippling. Talk to your doctor about other complications.  Talk to your doctor. For more information or to report a problem with Natrelle® Breast Implants
column129: please call Allergan at 1-800-678-1605. Please also see the patient brochures at www.allergan.com/labeling/usa.htm.  Natrelle® Breast Implants are available by prescription only.   LATISSE® (bimatoprost ophthalmic solution) 0.03%  Important Information  Approved Use  LATISSE® is an FDA-approved treatment to grow eyelashes for people with inadequate or not enough lashes.  IMPORTANT SAFETY INFORMATION  If you use/used prescription products for eye pressure problems
column130: use LATISSE® under doctor care. May cause brown darkening of the colored part of the eye which is likely permanent. LATISSE® may cause eyelid skin darkening which may be reversible. Only apply at base of the upper lashes. DO NOT APPLY to lower lid. Hair may grow outside the treatment area. If you have eye problems/surgery
column131: consult your doctor. Common side effects include itchy and red eyes. If discontinued
column132: lashes gradually return to previous appearance.  To report a side effect

Weather Team in August 2011.  A New Jersey native
column2: she’s been interested in weather as long as she can remember. Research projects always included tornadoes and blizzards
column3: and she constantly tuned into The Weather Channel as a kid. Her favorite memory goes back to the Blizzard of 1996
column4: when she was up through all hours of the night taking hourly snow measurements at age 9.  Prior to WMTW
column5: Mallory worked at WHSV in Harrisonburg
column6: VA as the Executive Weather Producer and Morning Meteorologist for the award winning Daybreak morning show.  However
column7: her love of winter weather (and lack thereof in the Shenandoah Valley) brought her north to New England. You’ll probably catch her running or hiking in the warmer months and on the ski slopes during the winter.  Mallory graduated from the Pennsylvania State University in May 2008 with a Bachelor’s of Science in Meteorology and obtained the 449th CBM seal from the American Meteorological Society in September 2010. Now an avid college football fan
column8: you’ll find her glued to the TV during fall Saturdays as she cheers on her Nittany Lions.  ) (LOC Center) <SEP> (TYPE android.widget.LinearLayout) (TEXT ) (LOC Bottom) <SEP> (TYPE android.widget.RelativeLayout) (TEXT ) (LOC Bottom) <SEP> (TYPE android.widget.LinearLayout) (TEXT ) (LOC Bottom) <SEP> (TYPE android.widget.ImageView) (TEXT ) (LOC Bottom right) <SEP>
